# Task Manager Frontend - Implementation Walkthrough

## Summary

Successfully scaffolded and implemented the core frontend for the Task Manager SaaS application using React + TypeScript, Vite, and the approved architecture.

## What Was Built

### Project Structure

```
web/
├── src/
│   ├── app/
│   │   ├── App.tsx         # Root with providers (QueryClient, Router, Auth)
│   │   └── Router.tsx      # Protected/Public routes
│   ├── features/
│   │   ├── auth/           # Login, Signup, AuthProvider, authStore
│   │   ├── workspaces/     # Workspace pages, hooks, store
│   │   └── tasks/          # Task pages, list, form, hooks, realtime
│   ├── shared/
│   │   ├── components/
│   │   │   ├── ui/         # Button, Input, Label, Toast (shadcn pattern)
│   │   │   ├── layout/     # AppLayout, AuthLayout, Sidebar, Header
│   │   │   └── common/     # RichTextEditor (TipTap)
│   │   └── hooks/          # useToast, usePermission
│   ├── lib/
│   │   ├── supabase/       # client.ts, realtime.ts
│   │   └── query/          # TanStack Query client
│   ├── constants/          # queryKeys, permissions, routes
│   ├── types/              # database.ts, api.ts
│   └── styles/             # globals.css with Tailwind + CSS variables
└── config files            # package.json, vite.config.ts, tsconfig.json, etc.
```

### Key Features Implemented

| Feature | Description |
|---------|-------------|
| **Auth Flow** | Login/Signup with Supabase Auth, session persistence |
| **Workspaces** | List, create, workspace detail with task list |
| **Tasks** | List view, detail view, create/edit/delete with form |
| **TipTap Editor** | Rich text editing for task descriptions |
| **Realtime** | Supabase Realtime subscription hook ready |
| **Permission Hooks** | Role-based [usePermission](file:///e:/TDC_App/Task%20Management/web/src/shared/hooks/usePermission.ts#6-42) and [useTaskPermissions](file:///e:/TDC_App/Task%20Management/web/src/shared/hooks/usePermission.ts#43-63) |
| **State Management** | Zustand for client state, TanStack Query for server state |

